Uses of Class
fplogn.File

    • Uses of File in fplogn

      Subclasses of File in fplogn 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  Folder
      Folder class is just a File which is used to make the file's paths, then it's children Files have a reference to its parent Folder. essentially it's just like any other File, except that for being a parent of any File, it has to be a Folder.
      Methods in fplogn that return types with arguments of type File 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.util.LinkedList<File> FileStructure.getByExt(java.lang.String ext)
      Searches for all the Files with the given extension, the extension has to be written without the dot, and it's found in Files as: [filename].
      java.util.TreeSet<File> FileStructure.getByFolder(Folder folder)
      Searches all the Files with the given Folder as their parent.
      java.util.TreeSet<File> FileStructure.getByFolder(java.lang.String path)
      Searches all the Files inside the Folder with the given path.
      java.util.LinkedList<File> FileStructure.getByName(java.lang.String name)
      Searches for all Files with the given name.
      java.util.LinkedList<File> FileStructure.getBySize(java.lang.Long size)
      Searches for all Files with the given size.
      java.util.LinkedList<File> FileStructure.getByUser(java.lang.String user)
      Searches for all Files with the given user.
      java.util.SortedMap<java.lang.Long,java.util.LinkedList<File>> FileStructure.getHigherThan(java.lang.Long size)
      Returns a SortedMap representing the part of the Tree with size higher than or equal to the given size.
      java.util.SortedMap<java.lang.Long,java.util.LinkedList<File>> FileStructure.getLessThan(java.lang.Long size)
      Returns a SortedMap representing the part of the Tree wich has less or equal size than the given size.
      Methods in fplogn with parameters of type File 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean FileStructure.add(File file)
      Adds the given File (if not repeated) to all the trees in this class, allowing to search it with complexity O(log(n)) (n being the number of Files in the FileStructure) by name, size, extension, user and its parent folder's path.
